		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0"><tr><td colspan="2"><font class="h1font">Merry Goblinday</font></td></tr><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Rating</Font></TD><TD><table width='92' border='0' cellspacing='0' cellpadding='0'><tr><td background='/lotr/gfx/5star.gif'><img src='/lotr/gfx/trans.gif' width='1' height='25'></td></tr></table><font size=1>(4.58)</font> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=21518&PHPSESSID=1eaba39bc76a16dc32d1dc04bba385a6">Read Reviews</A></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Author</font></TD><TD><font class="bfont"> <A HREF="http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=8062">Michael "Big Yoda" Walklate</A></FONT> <font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=8062&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a></font></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Description</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> A cheap deck that only uses four rares. It looks like a Hobbit deck but has lots of expendable companions to take the big hits. Also a goblin swarm with sharp bits.</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Submitted</Font></TD><TD><font class="bfont"> February 18, 2002</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Cards</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Starting<br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(175)">Frodo, Son of Drogo</a><br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(182)">The One Ring, The Ruling Ring</a><br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(185)">Merry, From O&#39;er the Brandywine</a><br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(307)">Boromir, Son of Denethor</a><br />
<br />
Adventure Deck<br />
[1] <a href="javascript:card_browser(205)">The Prancing Pony</a><br />
