<a href="javascript:card_browser(86)">Moria Scout</a> x4<br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(75)">Goblin Scimitar</a> x3<br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(82)">Host of Thousands</a> x4<br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(91)">They Are Coming</a><br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(78)">Goblin Swarms</a><br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(98)">Unfamiliar Territory</a> x2<br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(65)">Frenzy</a><br />
<a href="javascript:card_browser(89)">Relentless</a>    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> This was the deck I took to a tournament on sunday and it only lost one game on the day. It is cheap and easy to play like some of my friends.<br />
<br />
The crucial thing it to get some swords out. Once your hobbits have swords they are tanks. Merry becomes 7 and can be 10 when Boromir exerts, add in some There and Back Again, Dagger Strikes and Hobbit Intuition and even the Balrog needs to watch out! He beat up the Witch King twice at the tournamet.<br />
<br />
Card choices:<br />
-Boromir prevents Hobbits being overwhelmed as does the Bounder. <br />
-I find the later sights more scary so go for Hobbit Intuition and +3 over Hobbit Stealth.<br />
-4x There and Back Again? Can still be used even against Saruman&#39;s Snows. Not much else can. Makes ALL of your Hobbits +2.<br />
-Aragon is fantastic and can heal Merry or Sam each turn. <br />
-PATHS is huge in any deck.<br />
-Gandalf, Legolas, Sam and Pippin are all expendable. Pippin especially seems to love to fight really huge minions :-(<br />
<br />
Shadow<br />
Fairly standard. Very cheap goblins come out in swarms. By using Scavengers, Host of Thousands, Goblin Swarms and They Are Coming you can potentially use your scimitars ten to twenty times. (Adding 2 str and drawing a new card every time for cost 0.)<br />
<br />
Scouts are often free and soak archery. Runners are better than free. Wall crawlers reduce archery and are good value underground. Marksmen shoot - need I say more. The Goblin Partol Groups are str 13 with three wounds. They are like easy to use trolls. It can be amazing how often the fellowship has to fight them once ...Swarms or ...Coming is out.<br />
<br />
Relentless and Frenzy while generally not that useful can catch the unsuspecting or careless player and potentially turn around a game. Nice to have one for a rainy day.<br />
<br />
Locations<br />
TPP downloads Aragon. Lots of possessions and Hobbits so in go Trollshaw Forest and Frodo&#39;s Bedroom. Dimrill Dale and Shores of NH go in to boost the shadow strategy. Seeing I don&#39;t have much archery on either side Anduin Wilderness is good either way. At the Summit of Amon Hen each card dawn is potentially another Goblin I can afford to put down for the final battle. Non-goblin players are often limited by the cost not cards.<br />
<br />
I am sure that this deck is far from perfect but I have very limited cards at this stage and it worked so well on the weekend I thought I would record it at least so I can look back on it in a couple of years time.<br />
<br />
I hope all of you have a Merry Goblinday. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/lotr/decks/decks.php?PHPSESSID=1eaba39bc76a16dc32d1dc04bba385a6">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=21518&PHPSESSID=1eaba39bc76a16dc32d1dc04bba385a6"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=21518&PHPSESSID=1eaba39bc76a16dc32d1dc04bba385a6" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/lotr/main/join.php?PHPSESSID=1eaba39bc76a16dc32d1dc04bba385a6">Sign up for free!</A></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
